ConstrainedDoubleDiscreteParameterEditor

public ConstrainedDoubleDiscreteParameterEditor()
No-Arg constructor calls super();

ConstrainedDoubleDiscreteParameterEditor

public ConstrainedDoubleDiscreteParameterEditor(ParameterAPI model)
                                         throws ConstraintException
Sets the model in this constructor. The parameter is checked that it is a DoubleDiscreteParameter, and the constraint is checked that it is a DoubleDiscreteConstraint. Then the constraints are checked that there is at least one. If any of these fails an error is thrown.

The widget is then added to this editor, based on the number of constraints. If only one the editor is made into a non-editable label, else a picklist of values to choose from are presented to the user. A tooltip is given to the name label if model info is available.

setParameter

public void setParameter(ParameterAPI model)
                  throws ConstraintException
Can change the parameter of this editor. Usually called once when initializing the editor. The parameter is checked that it is a DoubleDiscreteParameter, and the constraint is checked that it is a DoubleDiscreteConstraint. Then the constraints are checked that there is at least one. If any of these fails an error is thrown.

The widget is then added to this editor, based on the number of constraints. If only one the editor is made into a non-editable label, else a picklist of values to choose from are presented to the user. A tooltip is given to the name label if model info is available.
